< text>
Hands down, best shop in town. My Dad went in to get a new stereo, backup camera, remote start etc put into his truck. We went with him just because my husband and I are more techy than he is so we could explain something later if need be. Brandon, I believe his name is, the owner, is incredible. They sat with my Dad to make sure to go through the system and teach him everything about it. They made sure he knew that he could call or come in with questions, anytime. My husband and I wanted to update our system, just for our own piece of mind, went and received quotes from other stereo shops and let me tell you, the customer service doesn't even compare to the staff of Simply Auto Sound. We will absolutely be making an appointment with this establishment for our stereo needs. Thanks for being amazing guys!< /text>

< text>
Yay! First review! This place is great. They have so many amazing and unique ice cream choices because they make nearly all of it themselves. They let you sample them all if you want which is great because you've probably never had those flavors before. The portions are great for their prices and the quality is fantastic too. The staff is fun as well. My girlfriend and I love this place. It's a little hidden behind a bank so it doesn't stand out which is a shame for such a good place. It's a neat little place and definitely worth checking out if you like ice cream.<//text>

<Time>1615235040731<//Time>< rate>

<Text>I went there because of my son... he kept mentioning it so I walked in to get him a treat one day and i spent my time waiting in line trying to figure out the drinks. The best thing was just asking the staff behind the counter to customize any drink to your tastes. Since it was my first time in, i got a variety of drinks and different flavors of Boba. Being Asian, I had my share of Boba and these are definitely differently made and have nice different flavors. I liked that the flavors were not overwhelming (like some you get when they use too much flavoring) yet have that subtle taste and aftertaste that is pleasant on the palate. I might not know how to cook like a Michelin star chef but I like to think I know how to appreciate good food and deserts. Definitely a spot to check out if you are within pickup distance. Definitely a trip worth taking if you "just need to go somewhere" too! :) Cheers.< /Text><Pics>None</Pics><Resp>None< /Resp>< GmapID>

<Review>I have been dying to have one boba shop in this plaza and it's finally happening!! One Zo boba shop opened right next to the LA Fitness!! What a love hate relationship!! Do I want to work out first so I can drink this boba???

The store has really cute decoration and extremely friendly staff. I was really hesitant about roast rice milk tea. I love roast rice tea but I was conflicted about roast rice tea with Milk. The staff saw I was so struggling and offered to make me one test sample. I don't like to waste food but she was so welcoming. After the sample, I definitely fell in love with this taste and I bought the rest of the sample. I love the store has such hard working and friendly staff, go on beyond her work to promote the products she is confident with. Sorry I didn't catch her name.

The fresh made boba here is incredible!! Super fresh and chewy. The only downside is the price is $5 plus for the whole drink, probably because of the location. The cup is not really big for the price.

<Review>Here in Orange County there is no shortage of boba shops so it‚Äôs important to make sure that the one you go to is a memorable one.

For me, it can be classified by a couple determining factors:
- Customer Service
- Menu and Variety
- Taste (obviously)
- Value

CUSTOMER SERVICE
I wanted to touch upon this as this was the one most lacking. Yes, the cashiers smiled at me when I was placing the order but it was one of those situations where they do it because they have to and not because they are genuinely excited to serve you. Maybe I‚Äôm being too nit-picky for this, but authenticity is important and they lost a star from me for not having it.

MENU AND VARIETY
Now the menu here was a bit interesting. The menu wasn‚Äôt incredibly extensive but for example, their brown sugar options alone came with 6 different options. I had also never seen a black charcoal latte before and I thought that was rather unique.

The variety, though, comes from their handmade boba. This is the first boba shop I have been to where the store actually makes it for you onsite. And not like the kind where you buy them in bags and boil it in there. So they get some kudos for this one! If you look closely, their store made boba is more expensive than their other bobas. I can appreciate a place that has more than just regular or honey boba to offer.

TASTE
I opted for the simple milk tea with one zo boba in the honey flavor at 50% sweetness and 50% ice. I was a bit disappointed because the menu clearly says milk tea OR green milk tea but I still ended up with the green one (I‚Äôm a huge black milk tea fan.) I wanted a light sweetness so I could taste that extra honey infused boba. The result? Meh. I have been to plenty other stores with milk tea and honey boba and this one did not impress me.

VALUE
Now to be completely fair, tea drinks in Orange County are in the $4-6 range but because One Zo has specialty drinks with house made boba they are obviously in the more expensive range. End result? 3/5.

‚Äî
Overall, One Zo does have a bit to offer. I think if I came in with someone that really knew what to order or if the cashiers could tell me a little bit more about their menu I would have likely ordered something that I would have truly loved. Needless to say, it isn‚Äôt the closest shop to me so I can‚Äôt say I‚Äôm gonna miss out on this one.<//Review><Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPItScekz1vNGt4wZO2IhmjLnOJCQCbgKFJM6_K=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPR1JKFGCG6ajZsE6ufMWvJV6VTJYgQsu3FOM-0=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipM7HgWpnlZdaM64pCLoh5vGmnnVzOUARKcwYqT0=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNJ25GRKDhLDOHC8zOq549VYWwSxZo-aH87Psb4=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipM__c_XkqKf45f-xqh-O4q7YXjxDyDApA10_0b-=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNU7zLyP5DeF3YdLumBEg0HtpN6tFrqQxYvc1MD=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</Pics><response>None<//response><gmap_id>0x80dcdd68cbc85895:0x1b4ed0cbd9aa5dff</gmap_id></record>

<pics>None<//pics>< review>
Short hours, extended equipment downtime, many holidays, far too busy.
Cable machines break several times per year (cables fray) and it is not uncommon for a month or longer to pass before they are fixed. Often, both will be broken machines in the MAC will be broken simultaneously. The facility is far too small for the number of members, and it's not uncommon to wait 15-20 minutes for a barbell/squat rack/bench press. Hours are short (close at 9:00 PM on weekends, open at 6:30 AM on weekdays) and they are closed a large number of days out of the year.<//review>

< review>
I'm sure there food would be as good as any other Yogis but this place uses CHEAP black Styrofoam containers that leaked flavours into my food. When I called to let them know about the Styrofoam taste they were very nice and offered a refund but I was unable to collect because of my short lunch break. i believe the workers are doing a great job but the management NEEDS to get containers that are better quality. For the record I still eat Yogis just not from this location.

< name>
Alex Tokash< /name>
<GmapID>0x80dd29979a70cd89:0xf2b6ab219cc3e0c0< /GmapID>< rate>
5</rate>
< Text>
When I entered this small store at 7:30pm on a Sunday evening it was busy.  The few tables that were inside were all occupied and several people were ahead of me who had already ordered. The girl behind the counter was dealing with and assembling multiple orders yet I was surprised that she turned around for a moment to acknowledge me with a smile letting me know she would be with me.  Then two cooks behind the counter in the kitchen who looked like twins or at least brothers both made eye contact with me and also gave me smiles.   After placing my order with the girl, I stood to the side by the trash bin next to the entry into the kitchen. An older gentleman who looked like he may have been the owner or at least a manager invited me with a smile to sit down at a table while I wait.  Total wait time was around 10 minutes when I finally got my food which I took to go.  I ordered a large chicken beef veggie combo. I thought it was delicious.  The chicken was tender, the beef was flavorful, the rice was soft and sticky with no hard under-cooked pieces and the veggies were plentiful which included cabbage, carrots, and broccoli. They offered extra sauces for free which included teriyaki, Louisiana, and chili as well as other condiments like ginger, jalapenos, and green onions.  For the price and what is offered, especially considering the free condiments, it's a good value. No it's not dirt cheap but this is 2017 folks, you're not going to find cheap food when eating out anymore.
I got my food in the large black container and tasted no residual flavors as one reviewer complained.
This was my first visit and I will definitely be visiting again.</Text>

< Text>
As much as I wanted to give Junk King a higher rating, my experience was far from seamless in what was already a stressful situation. Before booking for junk removal, I think everyone should at least know what to expect, so that they can avoid running through the same issues as I did.

After getting the news of my grandfather being transferred to hospice, and having to move my grandmother to live with us on short notice, we had to work as quickly as possible to clean out their house. Since it was my first time using a junk removal service, I called around to get a quote that would fit our budget. After meeting with several companies, it was down to Fred‚Äôs Junk Removal or Junk King.

Fred‚Äôs Junk Removal had a flat rate, but because I met the Junk King representatives in person and they seemed very nice and willing to work with our budget, I decided to book an appointment with them (plus, it doesn‚Äôt hurt when they have a guarantee to beat any written estimate). I tried calling the rep that had given me the quote, but it went to voicemail and indicated that I should call the San Diego call center for appointments.

After explaining the situation with my quote reference (2 pickup trucks, including some furniture removal) and telling the agent about Fred‚Äôs comparable 3 pickup truck flat rate of $297, I was put on hold so that the call center rep can make some calls for approval. When she got back to me with a price match of $295, I was relieved. I made sure to verify all the info and she confirmed that was the price for the job.

On the day of my appointment, I got Oscar (who I had met previously when I got my quote) and Fernando. According to Fernando, the confirmed quote I got from the call center didn‚Äôt match the one they had down, but rather the old estimate. After talking to his boss, he re-quoted me with $570, saying I already had a steal for that price and was free to go with Fred‚Äôs Junk Removal if I wanted to because they are busy and I was wasting their time. I felt like I was put in a bind to quickly make a decision, because not only did we had to clear the house by that day and catch a flight home right after, we now missed the opportunity to book with a cheaper option since it was so last minute. Had I known there were so much miscommunication within the company, where confirmation for details and prices of the job aren‚Äôt matching up and was even told that the call center ‚Äúdon‚Äôt know anything‚Äù, I would have went with a different company.

So before you book your appointment, make sure you aren‚Äôt on a time scrunch and confirm what the entire job entails, because you might have to pay more than you have to. The one star is for the speediness because they were able to knock it out in a short amount of time.<//Text>

<rating>1<//rating>< Text>
As much as I wanted to give Junk King a higher rating, my experience was far from seamless in what was already a stressful situation. Before booking for junk removal, I think everyone should at least know what to expect, so that they can avoid running through the same issues as I did.

After getting the news of my grandfather being transferred to hospice, and having to move my grandmother to live with us on short notice, we had to work as quickly as possible to clean out their house. Since it was my first time using a junk removal service, I called around to get a quote that would fit our budget. After meeting with several companies, it was down to Fred‚Äôs Junk Removal or Junk King.

Fred‚Äôs Junk Removal had a flat rate, but because I met the Junk King representatives in person and they seemed very nice and willing to work with our budget, I decided to book an appointment with them (plus, it doesn‚Äôt hurt when they have a guarantee to beat any written estimate). I tried calling the rep that had given me the quote, but it went to voicemail and indicated that I should call the San Diego call center for appointments.

After explaining the situation with my quote reference (2 pickup trucks, including some furniture removal) and telling the agent about Fred‚Äôs comparable 3 pickup truck flat rate of $297, I was put on hold so that the call center rep can make some calls for approval. When she got back to me with a price match of $295, I was relieved. I made sure to verify all the info and she confirmed that was the price for the job.

On the day of my appointment, I got Oscar (who I had met previously when I got my quote) and Fernando. According to Fernando, the confirmed quote I got from the call center didn‚Äôt match the one they had down, but rather the old estimate. After talking to his boss, he re-quoted me with $570, saying I already had a steal for that price and was free to go with Fred‚Äôs Junk Removal if I wanted to because they are busy and I was wasting their time. I felt like I was put in a bind to quickly make a decision, because not only did we had to clear the house by that day and catch a flight home right after, we now missed the opportunity to book with a cheaper option since it was so last minute. Had I known there were so much miscommunication within the company, where confirmation for details and prices of the job aren‚Äôt matching up and was even told that the call center ‚Äúdon‚Äôt know anything‚Äù, I would have went with a different company.

So before you book your appointment, make sure you aren‚Äôt on a time scrunch and confirm what the entire job entails, because you might have to pay more than you have to. The one star is for the speediness because they were able to knock it out in a short amount of time.< /Text>

< text>
You know there's every once in a while you find that service provider, that is exactly as you had hoped, and requested. I was looking for a junk hauler this morning, via a Google search and Junk King San Diego popped up on Google. The verified the items to be hauled away, no issues. They loaded everything I needed into the truck and were very pleasant throughout. <text>USE JUNK KING AND FORGET ABOUT CALLING ANYONE ELSE. I received an email confirmation and CJ and Austin called me about 30 min. before my appointment, showed up ON TIME, were extremely professional, in Junk King shirts, polite, pleasant and walked me through the process.  I have had professional movers move and pack me several times, and i have to say, CJ and Austin surpassed my prior experiences - and this one was tough, emotionally hard, as my parents had lived in this home for decades.  CJ gave me a super fair estimate based on the total rooms and how many trucks would be needed, was transparent with me on their pricing, and once I accepted, they immediately went to work.  These guys DO NOT REST.  They move. FAST.  LIKE SUPER FAST.  They work HARD.
